parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in property damage and potentially harming the occupants. It can also lead to sudden acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The key is difficult to insert into the ignition
the key is hard to turn
the ignition switch sparks
the vehicle catches fire
smoke comes from the steering column
the horn blows unexpectedly
and the vehicle accelerates suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short in the Steering Column
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the steering column can cause the ignition switch to catch fire, resulting in property damage and potentially harming the occupants.
symptoms: Smoke comes from the steering column
flames start coming from the steering column
the ignition switch catches on fire
and the vehicle accelerates suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
stalls when slowing down or entering a ramp
stalls when using the air conditioning/heat or vent
stalls intermittently
and may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine failure, leading to accidents, and rusting can lead to engine compartment fires.
symptoms: Engine oil pan rusted out
causing engine oil leaks
oil pan rusting out from the inside out
engine head gaskets leaking oil
and fear of engine compartment fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause serious injury, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle fire
fear of engine compartment fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Gas Pedal Sticking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the brakes may not respond or are ineffective in slowing down the vehicle
the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied.
